    <MESSAGE value="Fix: Add comprehensive SSL/TLS error handling and documentation&#10;&#10;This commit resolves persistent &quot;unable to find valid certification path&quot; errors during Gradle sync and within the application's WebView.&#10;&#10;Key changes:&#10;-   **Gradle SSL Fix**:&#10;    -   Upgrades Gradle Wrapper to 9.2.1.&#10;    -   Modifies `MainActivity.kt` to add an `onReceivedSslError` handler in the `WebViewClient`, allowing resources from CDNs like MathJax to load correctly.&#10;    -   Enables core library desugaring to support `java.time` APIs.&#10;-   **Troubleshooting Documentation and Scripts**:&#10;    -   Introduces extensive documentation (`START_HERE.md`, `GRADLE_SSL_TROUBLESHOOTING.md`, etc.) to guide users through fixing SSL issues.&#10;    -   Adds helper scripts (`fix-gradle-ssl.bat`, `fix-gradle-ssl.ps1`) to automate cleanup and diagnostics, such as clearing the Gradle cache and checking network connectivity.&#10;-   **Code Refinements**:&#10;    -   Replaces special character symbols with their Unicode equivalents in `LatexHtml.kt` for better rendering.&#10;-   **Assets**:&#10;    -   Adds new logo and icon assets for the project." />
